data.title: Bread for Sandwiches
data.solution:
n = int(input())

s_type = {
    'BLT': 2,
    'Club': 3,
    'Sky': 5,
}

bread_count = {}
for _ in range(n):
    slices, sandwich = input().split(' ')
    slices = int(slices)
    bread_count[sandwich] = slices + bread_count.get(sandwich, 0)

blt_rem = bread_count.get('BLT', 0) % s_type['BLT']
club_rem = bread_count.get('Club', 0) % s_type['Club']
sky_rem = bread_count.get('Sky', 0) % s_type['Sky']


print(blt_rem)
print(club_rem)
print(sky_rem)
data.statement:
Determine how much of each type of sandwich bread is left over if the maximum possible number of sandwiches are made.  You are given [[N]] lines where each line has [[S]] slices of a loaf of bread and the type of sandwich the loaf is used for separated by a space.

The types of sandwiches each loaf can be used for are

{{BLT}} which uses 2 slices of bread
{{Club}} which uses 3 slices of bread
{{Sky}} which uses 5 slices of bread

Loaves of bread can be combined for sandwiches of the same type.
